 Ecology 3E</i></a>. Tata McGraw-Hill Education. p.&#160;213. <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1-259-08109-5" title="Special:BookSources/978-1-259-08109-5">978-1-259-08109-5</a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">18 October</span> 2013</span>. <q>Normally the human eye responds to light rays from 390 to 760 nm. This can be extended to a range of 310 to 1,050 nm under artificial conditions.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALight&amp;rft.au=Dash%2C+Satya+Prakash&amp;rft.aufirst=Madhab+Chandra&amp;rft.aulast=Dash&amp;rft.btitle=Fundamentals+Of+Ecology+3E&amp;rft.date=2009&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.isbn=978-1-259-08109-5&amp;rft.pages=213&amp;rft.pub=Tata+McGraw-Hill+Education&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D7mW4-us4Yg8C%26pg%3DPA213&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-Saidman1933-13"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Saidman1933_13-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation journal">Saidman, Jean (15 May 1933). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://visualiseur.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/bpt6k3148d">"Sur la visibilit\xc3\xa9 de l\'ultraviolet jusqu\'\xc3\xa0 la longueur d\'onde 3130"</a> [The visibility of the ultraviolet to the wave length of 3130]. <i><a href="/wiki/Comptes_rendus_de_l%27Acad%C3%A9mie_des_sciences" title="Comptes rendus de l\'Acad\xc3\xa9mie des sciences">Comptes rendus de l\'Acad\xc3\xa9mie des sciences</a></i> (in French). <b>196</b>: 1537\xe2\x80\x939.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALight&amp;rft.atitle=Sur+la+visibilit%C3%A9+de+l%27ultraviolet+jusqu%27%C3%A0+la+longueur+d%27onde+3130&amp;rft.aufirst=Jean&amp;rft.aul